Key Match Events: Milwaukee hosted the Spurs and sent them home with a 121-105 loss.
The Bucks never found themselves behind San Antonio on the scoreboard after an AJ Green three-pointer with 3:09 left in the first quarter.
Victor Wembanyama scored 10 points, grabbed 10 rebounds, and blocked three shots but finished with a -7 plus-minus stat.
Damian Lillard led the Bucks with 26 points, Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 25 points, and Brook Lopez had 22 points.
